nodes.documentation:
@title   EllipticCurve
 * @author  Tilman Drerup;
 * @notice  Implements elliptic curve math; Parametrized for SECP256R1.
 *          Includes components of code by Andreas Olofsson, Alexander Vlasov
         (https://github.com/BANKEX/CurveArithmetics), and Avi Asayag
         (https://github.com/orbs-network/elliptic-curve-solidity)
 * @dev     NOTE: To disambiguate public keys when verifying signatures, activate
         condition 'rs[1] > lowSmax' in validateSignature().
nodes.name: EllipticCurve

nodes.documentation: @dev Inverse of u in the field of modulo m.
nodes.name: inverseMod

nodes.documentation: @dev Transform affine coordinates into projective coordinates.
nodes.name: toProjectivePoint

nodes.documentation: @dev Transform from projective to affine coordinates.
nodes.name: toAffinePoint

nodes.documentation: @dev Return the zero curve in projective coordinates.
nodes.name: zeroProj

nodes.documentation: @dev Return the zero curve in affine coordinates.
nodes.name: zeroAffine

nodes.documentation: @dev Check if the curve is the zero curve.
nodes.name: isZeroCurve

nodes.documentation:
@dev Double an elliptic curve point in projective coordinates. See
https://www.nayuki.io/page/elliptic-curve-point-addition-in-projective-coordinates
nodes.name: twiceProj

nodes.documentation:
@dev Add two elliptic curve points in projective coordinates. See
https://www.nayuki.io/page/elliptic-curve-point-addition-in-projective-coordinates
nodes.name: addProj

nodes.documentation: @dev Helper function that splits addProj to avoid too many local variables.
nodes.name: addProj2

nodes.documentation: @dev Double an elliptic curve point in affine coordinates.
nodes.name: twice

nodes.documentation: @dev Multiply an elliptic curve point by a scalar.
nodes.name: multiplyScalar

typeDescriptions.typeString: function (bytes memory,bytes memory) pure returns (bytes memory)

nodes.documentation: @dev Multiply the curve's generator point by a scalar.
nodes.name: multipleGeneratorByScalar
